<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910626-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>910626-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- USA Waste Services Inc.:   Company Agrees to Acquire   A.R.F. Landfill for Stock</HL><DATE>06/26/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   USAS</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>ILLINOIS (IL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   USA Waste Services Inc. said it agreed to acquire A.R.F.Landfill Corp. for 4.5 million common shares, valued at about$57.4 million.   USA Waste, a solid-waste management company, said A.R.F.operates a non-hazardous landfill in Lake County, Ill., nearChicago. A.R.F. had pretax earnings of more than $3 millionon revenue of about $6.9 million for the fiscal year endedMarch 31.</LP><TEXT>   USA Waste currently has about four million sharesoutstanding. It said it plans to close the transaction, whichwill be treated as a pooling of interests acquisition, by theend of the month.   After the transaction, Robert F. Smith, owner of A.R.F.,will be USA Waste's largest shareholder and will become vicechairman of the board, increasing the board's size to sixmembers.   Earl E. DeFrates, vice president, finance, for USA Waste,said the landfill has plenty of room to grow and there wereseveral bidders for it. He said the acquisition &quot;probablywill be the cornerstone of building this company.&quot;   USA Waste had net income of $202,000, or five cents ashare, on revenue of $1.5 million for the first quarter. Itsstock closed at $12.75 bid, up $1.125 in over-the-countertrading yesterday.</TEXT></DOC>